<item>
            <title>[SOLR-266] Let the LukeRequestHandler return parsed schema information</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-266</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The LukeRequestHandler currently just shows info for fields it finds in the index.  It could also show info for fields in the schema.  This patch adds:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  &lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8983/solr/admin/luke?show=schema&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8983/solr/admin/luke?show=schema&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;showing a list of all fields defined by the schema followed by the types and what fields use the types (if any)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is helpful for client apps to know what fields are available and is also a good sanity check to see what fields solr knows about after parsing the schema.xml.  Chasing down xml parsing can be difficult:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nabble.com/Keep-having-error-on-%22unknown-field%22-tf3923356.html#a11125764&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.nabble.com/Keep-having-error-on-%22unknown-field%22-tf3923356.html#a11125764&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
